The paper discusses the use of deep learning frameworks for segmentation of vasculature in microscopy images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional networks, which is a common technique in deep learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the architecture of the network, which could fall under neural networks (cs.NE) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with microscopy images, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
